Then CNN combines all channels:

314+(−175)+326+Bias(1)

Final Output:

466

The value 466 becomes one pixel in the output feature map.

Why Is This Useful?

This calculation helps CNN identify patterns.

Example:

| Filter Learns  | Detects                |
| -------------- | ---------------------- |
| Edge filter    | Borders of objects     |
| Texture filter | Fabric patterns        |
| Shape filter   | Eyes, wheels, shirts   |
| Color filter   | Specific color regions |


