Real-Time Example

Suppose you are building:

Fashion Product Classifier

CNN learns:

Shirt collars
Shoe shapes
Bag outlines
Trouser textures

Instead of manually programming these features, CNN automatically learns them using these convolution calculations.

Why Different Kernels?

Different kernels detect different features.

Example:

One kernel detects vertical edges
Another detects horizontal edges
Another detects textures

That’s why CNN uses many filters.

